  - chaos engineering
abstract: "We introduce Mean Time to Epistemic Failure (MTEF), the first temporal reliability metric for measuring how long autonomous AI systems maintain factual coherence under iterative processing. Through controlled telephone-game experiments across four major language model architectures, we demonstrate that multi-agent AI systems exhibit predictable epistemic decay following quantifiable thermodynamic regimes. Our principal finding—the Autoimmune Paradox—reveals that governed systems decay 2.2x faster than ungoverned systems."
